PREAMBLE

Vanadium OS is an open-source music playback operating system
developed by VV Audio Lab. This license grants you the freedom
to use, study, and modify the software, while protecting the
VV Audio Lab brand identity.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. GRANT OF RIGHTS

   Subject to the terms of this License, VV Audio Lab grants
   you a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to:

   a) Use Vanadium OS for personal and non-commercial purposes
   b) Study and examine the source code
   c) Modify the source code for personal use
   d) Distribute verbatim or modified copies, subject to
      Section 2 (Brand Protection Requirements)

2. BRAND PROTECTION REQUIREMENTS

   Any distribution of Vanadium OS, whether verbatim or
   modified, MUST comply with ALL of the following:

   a) LOGO RETENTION
      The VV Audio Lab and VVAI logos, as provided in the
      /assets/logo/ directory, must be retained in all
      distributed versions. Logos must not be:
      - Removed or hidden
      - Replaced with other logos or graphics
      - Altered, distorted, or recolored
      - Reduced in size below the minimum specified dimensions

   b) BRAND ATTRIBUTION
      All distributed versions must display, in a prominent
      location visible during normal use:
      "Powered by Vanadium OS — VV Audio Lab"

   c) COPYRIGHT NOTICE
      All source files must retain the original copyright
      notice:
      "Copyright (C) 2026 VV Audio Lab. All rights reserved."

   d) ABOUT SCREEN
      The About / Credits screen must include:
      - "Vanadium OS by VV Audio Lab"
      - A link or reference to vvaudiolab.com
      - The original version number and release date

3. PERMITTED MODIFICATIONS

   You are free to modify the following without restriction:

   a) Playback engine settings (MPD, Roon Bridge, Diretta)
   b) Audio output configuration
   c) Network and system settings
   d) UI color themes and visual styles
      (provided brand elements in Section 2 are retained)
   e) Additional features and plugins
   f) Language and localization

4. COMMERCIAL USE RESTRICTIONS

   Commercial use of Vanadium OS requires a separate written
   license from VV Audio Lab. "Commercial use" includes but
   is not limited to:

   a) Selling hardware pre-loaded with Vanadium OS
   b) Offering Vanadium OS as part of a paid service
   c) Using Vanadium OS in products sold to end customers
   d) Sublicensing Vanadium OS to third parties

   To obtain a commercial license, contact:
   VV Audio Lab — vvaudiolab.com

5. CONTRIBUTIONS

   Contributions to Vanadium OS are welcome. By submitting
   a contribution, you agree that:

   a) Your contribution will be licensed under this License
   b) VV Audio Lab retains the right to include, modify,
      or reject contributions
   c) You have the legal right to make the contribution

6. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY

   Vanadium OS is provided "AS IS", without warranty of any
   kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the
   warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular
   purpose, and non-infringement.

   In no event shall VV Audio Lab or its contributors be
   liable for any claim, damages, or other liability arising
   from the use of this software.

7. TERMINATION

   Your rights under this License will terminate automatically
   if you fail to comply with any of its terms, particularly
   the Brand Protection Requirements in Section 2.

   Upon termination, you must cease all distribution of
   Vanadium OS and destroy all copies in your possession.

8. GOVERNING LAW

   This License shall be governed by and construed in
   accordance with applicable international copyright law.

